-- Putin orders cash from wealth fund to be used to support banks 
-- By Moscow Newsroom
-- Thu Dec 04, 2014 05:09AM EST
-- None



MOSCOW, Dec 4 (Reuters) - Russian President Vladimir Putin said on Thursday that money collected in one of the country's two rainy day funds should be used for supporting domestic banks.

As of Nov. 1. the National Wealth Fund, aimed at covering future pension shortages, stood at $81.7 billion.